## Plan

**Approach:** Add an OPTIONAL `OccurredAt time.Time` (json `occurred_at`,
omitempty) to the run manifest — manifest-wide so the round-trip stays in one
place, but EXPOSED only through `retro capture`/`generate` via a new
`--occurred-at <RFC3339>` flag. It is the canonical machine-readable event-time
for retros (when the retro's events actually happened), distinct from the
existing REQUIRED `Created` (capture/migration time). It stays optional and
backward-compatible: a manifest with no `occurred_at` (every existing retro and
run) remains valid and `OccurredAt.IsZero()` is true, so `show`/`log` fall back
to `created`. Runs keep using real capture time (no flag plumbed into the run
path). This bead adds the CAPABILITY + DISPLAY only; it does NOT backfill
existing retros (that is etude-8hq.5).

**Manifest field decision (optional + backward-compat proof):**
- Add `OccurredAt time.Time` to `Manifest` struct (internal/runmanifest/manifest.go:42,
  next to `Created`). Add `OccurredAt string \`json:"occurred_at,omitempty"\`` to
  `manifestJSON` (manifest.go:765, next to `Created`).
- Marshal (`toJSON`, manifest.go:933-942): set `OccurredAt: formatTimeOmitZero(m.OccurredAt)`
  — a small helper that returns `""` for a zero time (so omitempty drops the key)
  and `formatTime(t)` otherwise. Do NOT reuse `formatTime` directly: `formatTime`
  on a zero time emits `"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"`, which would defeat omitempty and
  pollute every existing-shaped retro. The helper is the load-bearing detail.
- Unmarshal (`toManifest`, manifest.go:1045): when `m.OccurredAt == ""` leave
  `OccurredAt` as the zero `time.Time`; otherwise `parseTime("occurred_at", m.OccurredAt)`
  and surface a parse error. (parseTime already returns UTC, RFC3339Nano —
  manifest.go:1234.)
- `Validate` (manifest.go:200): add NO new required check. `Created` stays
  required (:210-211); `OccurredAt` is never validated as required. Optionally add
  a defensive non-required sanity check only if non-zero (not needed — parseTime
  already guarantees a valid instant; skip to keep the diff minimal).
- BACKWARD-COMPAT PROOF: existing manifests have no `occurred_at` key. `ParseJSON`
  uses `DisallowUnknownFields` (manifest.go:274) — adding `occurred_at` to the
  KNOWN `manifestJSON` struct means old docs (which simply lack the key) still
  decode; an unknown field would only break if we encountered a key NOT in the
  struct, which is not the case. Absent key ⇒ `m.OccurredAt == ""` ⇒ zero
  `time.Time` ⇒ omitted on re-marshal ⇒ byte-identical round-trip for every
  existing retro/run. No manifest_version bump needed (the change is purely
  additive-optional; v2/v3 manifests stay v2/v3). Round-trip test will assert a
  v2 retro with no occurred_at re-serializes unchanged.

**Capture surface decision:**
- Add `occurredAt string` to `retroCaptureConfig` (retro.go:37) and
  `retroGenerateConfig` (retro.go:59), and `occurredAt string` to `retroWriteParams`
  (retro.go:83).
- Flag name: `--occurred-at` (RFC3339 timestamp string). Register on BOTH
  `retro capture` (retro.go:425, near `--meta-file`) and `retro generate`
  (retro.go:807) — generate produces the same retro artifact shape and the same
  backfill/cadence use case applies, so it needs the flag for symmetry. Help text:
  "original event time the retro covers, as RFC3339 (optional; defaults to capture
  time in displays when absent)".
- Validation: in `assembleAndWriteRetro` (retro.go:608), when `p.occurredAt != ""`,
  parse with `time.Parse(time.RFC3339, strings.TrimSpace(p.occurredAt))` and on
  error return `--occurred-at "<v>" is not a valid RFC3339 timestamp: <err>`
  BEFORE allocating the retro id / writing any ref. Set
  `manifest.OccurredAt = parsed.UTC()` (retro.go:734-741). When empty, leave
  `OccurredAt` zero. Wire `occurredAt: cfg.occurredAt` into both the capture
  `retroWriteParams` (retro.go:545) and the generate `retroWriteParams`
  (retro.go:935). (Parse uses RFC3339 not RFC3339Nano for the user-facing input so
  a plain `2026-05-20T00:00:00Z` is accepted; RFC3339Nano-format input also parses
  under RFC3339's grammar.)

**show decision (retro.go:290 printRetroDetail):**
- After the `created:` line (retro.go:302), add — only when
  `!m.OccurredAt.IsZero()`:
  `fmt.Fprintf(out, "occurred:  %s\n", m.OccurredAt.UTC().Format(time.RFC3339))`.
  Label `occurred:` sits alongside `created:`; both are shown so capture time is
  never lost. Absent ⇒ line omitted ⇒ existing retros render exactly as before.
- `retro list` (retro.go:179): leave the table columns unchanged for this bead
  (adding a column churns every list test/doc and the acceptance targets `show`
  + `log`, not `list`). Note this as a deliberate scope boundary.

**log decision (the load-bearing acceptance — internal/cli/log.go):**
- `etude log` must "distinguish or sort/display event time without losing capture
  time." Chosen behavior: introduce an EVENT-TIME column and sort by event-time,
  with capture time still shown.
  - `logEvent` (log.go:16): add `Occurred time.Time` field. In `buildEvents`,
    for retros set `Occurred: manifest.OccurredAt` (log.go:193); for runs leave it
    zero (runs have no occurred_at). The existing `Timestamp` field keeps holding
    `manifest.Created` (capture time) — capture time is NEVER dropped.
  - Add an `effectiveTime()` helper on `logEvent`: returns `Occurred` when
    `!Occurred.IsZero()`, else `Timestamp`. Sort (log.go:203-212) by
    `effectiveTime()` first, then break ties by `(Kind, ID)` exactly as today, so
    a backfilled retro with an `occurred_at` lands chronologically among the runs
    it retrospects instead of clustering at migration time.
  - Render (log.go:128-137) — **AMENDED per plan-gate-r1 codex BLOCK:** the
    `TIMESTAMP` column MUST keep showing `Timestamp` (= `manifest.Created`, the
    capture time) for EVERY row — NOT `effectiveTime()`. The original draft set
    `TIMESTAMP = effectiveTime()`, which for a backfilled retro displays
    `occurred_at` and HIDES `created`, violating the acceptance's "without losing
    capture time" (today `TIMESTAMP` is `created`, log.go:128/193, and docs/log.md:24
    promises it). Correct render: keep `TIMESTAMP` = capture time, ADD an `EVENT`
    column = `Occurred` when present else `-`, and SORT rows by `effectiveTime()`
    (occurred_at when present, else created). New header
    `TIMESTAMP\tKIND\tID\tEVENT\tSUMMARY`. Result: capture time is ALWAYS visible
    (`TIMESTAMP`), event time is visible when known (`EVENT`), and a backfilled
    retro lands chronologically (sorted by `effectiveTime`) among the runs it
    retrospects. The sort key (`effectiveTime`) is not itself a single displayed
    monotonic column — that is acceptable and standard (cf. git log sorting by
    commit date while showing author date); the EVENT column makes the ordering
    legible. Existing retros + all runs (no occurred_at) show `EVENT=-`, keep
    `TIMESTAMP=created`, and sort by created — byte-identical to today's output
    except for the added `EVENT=-` column (lock this with a golden-output test,
    per the Opus seat NIT).
  - Formatting NIT (Opus seat): the `EVENT` column must format with the SAME
    precision as the `TIMESTAMP` column (log.go:132 currently renders `Timestamp`
    at `RFC3339` second-precision) so the table is not ragged — render `Occurred`
    via the same formatter as `Timestamp`, not raw RFC3339Nano.
  - Rationale for column choice: the acceptance allows "distinguish OR sort/display";
    this does BOTH — distinguishes via the EVENT column and sorts via effective
    time — and is the most faithful to the bead's complaint that backfilled retros
    "cluster at migration time."

**PREMISE-CHECK — overlap with etude-8hq.3's sidecar `original_event_date`:**
8hq.3 (shipped, CLOSED) added a DOGFOOD-LAYER cadence retro-meta sidecar whose
7-key schema includes `original_event_date` ("YYYY-MM-DD" string), enforced ONLY
by `scripts/dogfood-completeness-audit.sh` check (f) — NOT by etude core
(docs/retro.md:61-110 explicitly states etude only checks `json.Valid` and stores
bytes verbatim). This bead (8hq.2) adds a CORE machine-readable
`occurred_at` timestamp on the manifest, surfaced by `show`/`log`.
RECONCILIATION (decision, no code/sidecar change here):
- The core `occurred_at` is the CANONICAL event time for etude-native tooling
  (manifest field, `retro show occurred:`, `etude log` EVENT column + sort).
- The sidecar `original_event_date` remains a HUMAN/DOGFOOD convenience (date-only,
  "YYYY-MM-DD") that downstream cross-retro analysis (etude-9ey) reads from the
  meta JSON. It is NOT removed or re-pointed by this bead.
- Relationship: `original_event_date` SHOULD mirror the date portion of
  `occurred_at` when both are set. They do not auto-sync (core does not parse the
  sidecar — that would violate 8hq.3/etude-2ku's verbatim posture). Precision
  differs by design: core = full RFC3339 instant; sidecar = calendar date.
- Forward note for etude-8hq.5 (backfill, the NEXT bead): 8hq.5 SHOULD set BOTH —
  `--occurred-at <RFC3339>` (core) AND the sidecar `original_event_date` via
  `--meta-file` — for each backfilled cadence retro, keeping the two coherent.
  This bead documents that expectation in docs/retro.md so the two do not silently
  diverge; it does not modify the audit or the sidecar convention (8hq.3 scope,
  shipped). The plan does NOT add core parsing/validation of the sidecar.

**Backward-compat + existing data:** All current retros/runs have no
`occurred_at` and stay valid (proof above). `retro show` omits the `occurred:`
line; `etude log` shows `EVENT=-` and sorts by capture time — identical to today
for un-backfilled data. No migration. No backfill (etude-8hq.5).

