**Risks:**
- formatTimeOmitZero is the make-or-break for backward compat: if a zero
  OccurredAt ever serializes a real timestamp, every existing retro's round-trip
  changes. Test (2) guards this directly.
- log EVENT-column header change will break any test asserting the exact header
  string — log_test.go must be updated in the same commit (listed above).
- `make docs` regen of the 3 generated CLI files must be committed or docs-check
  fails CI; flagged for IMPLEMENT. Low risk, mechanical.
- Premise risk (mitigated): must NOT make core parse/validate the sidecar
  `original_event_date` (would violate 8hq.3/etude-2ku verbatim posture). The plan
  keeps occurred_at and the sidecar fully independent; only docs note the
  should-mirror relationship.

